      ' Narrated Ibn `Umar:\n\nAllahs Messenger (ﷺ) had a silver ring made for himself and it was worn by him on his hand. Afterwards it was worn by Abu Bakr, and then by `Umar, and then by `Uthman till it fell in the Aris well. (On that ring) was engraved: Muhammad, the Messenger of Allah.',
