      ' Narrated `Aisha:\n\nAllahs Messenger (ﷺ) returned from a journey when I had placed a curtain of mine having pictures over (the door of) a chamber of mine. When Allahs Messenger (ﷺ) saw it, he tore it and said, The people who will receive the severest punishment on the Day of Resurrection will be those who try to make the like of Allahs creations. So we turned it (i.e., the curtain) into one or two cushions.',
