    hadithEnglish:
      ' Narrated Abu Talha:\n\nAllahs Messenger (ﷺ) said, Angels (of mercy) do not enter a house where there are pictures. The subnarrator Busr added: Then Zaid fell ill and we paid him a visit. Behold! There was, hanging at his door, a curtain decorated with a picture. I said to Ubaidullah Al-Khaulani, the step son of Maimuna, the wife of the Prophet (ﷺ) , Didnt Zaid tell us about the picture the day before yesterday? Ubaidullah said, Didnt you hear him saying: except a design in a garment?',
