      ' Narrated `Aisha:\n\n(the wife of the Prophet) A group of Jews entered upon the Prophet (ﷺ) and said, As-Samu-Alaikum. (i.e. death be upon you). I understood it and said, Wa-Alaikum As-Samu wal-lan. (death and the curse of Allah be Upon you). Allahs Messenger (ﷺ) said Be calm, O `Aisha! Allah loves that on, should be kind and lenient in all matters. I said, O Allahs Messenger (ﷺ)! Havent you heard what they (the Jews) have said? Allahs Messenger (ﷺ) said I have (already) said (to them) And upon you ! ',
