    hadithEnglish:
      ' Narrated Anas bin Malik:\n\nAllahs Messenger (ﷺ) said, If Adams son had a valley full of gold, he would like to have two valleys, for nothing fills his mouth except dust. And Allah forgives him who repents to Him.\n\nUbayy said (referring to the hadith above), We considered this as a saying from the Quran till the Surah (beginning with):\nThe mutual rivalry (for piling up of worldly things) diverts you (102:1) was revealed.',
